                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d712">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1529: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-03T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 3, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 3—12:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>412. Consulate’s 408 October 2, 5 p.m.<note n="42" xml:id="d712fn42">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_662">p. 662</ref>.</note> A
                    member of the Council stated to me today that “some consideration” was being
                    given to soliciting the participation of the American Government in possible
                    operations by airplane of “impartial observers”. In fact I was asked concerning
                    the nearest posts where American military attachés were stationed. General
                    reference was made in this connection to our participation in the Manchurian
                    inquiry.</p>
                <p>While I am at present disinclined to think that there is anything in this I am
                    reporting what was said to me.</p>
                <p>I feel it would be useful in a general sense to have as background the
                    Department’s comments. Please instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
